<faqs title="Developers Frequently Asked Questions">

  <part id="dev-faq-maven-usage">
    <title>odt2daisy developers faq (Maven Usage)</title>
    <faq id="dev-faq-maven-sourcecode">
      <question>
        How can I checkout odt2daisy sources ?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>You should visit this page: <a href="source-repository.html">Source repository</a>.</p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
    <faq id="dev-faq-maven-sf-settings">
      <question>
        How can I configure SF.net maven settings ?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>You have to copy/edit m2-settings.xml and merge it with your settings.xml</p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
    <faq id="dev-faq-maven-website-local">
      <question>
        How can I deploy the odt2daisy Maven Website locally ?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>You can type in your terminal:</p>
	<source>mvn clean site:site site:run</source>
        <p>The open with your favorite Web Browser this url: <a href="http://localhost:8080/">http://localhost:8080/</a>.</p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
    <faq id="dev-faq-maven-website-sf">
      <question>
        How can I deploy the odt2daisy Maven Website on SF.net ?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>First, create an ssh tunnel by typing in your terminal:</p>
	<source>ssh -t &lt;username&gt;,odt2daisy@shell.sourceforge.net create</source>
        <p>Then, deploy it by typing in your terminal:</p>
	<source>mvn clean site:site site:deploy</source>
      </answer>
    </faq>
    <faq id="dev-faq-maven-release-sf">
      <question>
        How can I release odt2daisy on SF.net ?
      </question>
      <answer>
        <p>First, create an ssh tunnel by typing in your terminal:</p>
	<source>ssh -t &lt;username&gt;,odt2daisy@shell.sourceforge.net create</source>
        <p>Then, release it by typing in your terminal the following commands:</p>
	<source>
	 mvn clean release:prepare
	 mvn release:perform</source>
	<p>
	  This will perform the following tasks:
	  <ul>
	    <li>Check that there are no uncommitted changes in the sources</li>
	    <li>Check that there are no SNAPSHOT dependencies</li>
	    <li>Change the version in the POMs from x-SNAPSHOT to a new version 
	      (you will be prompted for)</li>
	    <li>Transform the SCM information in the POM to include the final destination of the tag</li>
	    <li>Run the project tests against the modified POMs to confirm everything is in working order</li>
	    <li>Commit the modified POMs</li>
	    <li>Tag the code in the SCM with a version name (this will be prompted for)</li>
	    <li>Bump the version in the POMs to a new value y-SNAPSHOT (these values will also be prompted for)</li>
	    <li>Commit the modified POMs</li>
          </ul>
	  <ul>
	    <li>Checkout from an SCM URL with optional tag</li>
	    <li>Run the predefined Maven goals to release the project (deploy site-deploy)</li>
	  </ul>
	</p>
      </answer>
    </faq>
  </part>
